# Component Structure Rules

When creating or modifying components in `app/src/components`, follow this structure.

## Directory Layout

```
app/src/components/
├── {category}/           # data-display, data-visualization, dev-tools, feedback,
│                         # filters, form, general, illustrations, layout, special
│   └── {component-name}/
│       ├── index.ts      # Public exports only
│       ├── the-component/
│       │   ├── index.tsx # Main component + types
│       │   └── styles.module.scss
│       ├── README.md     # Optional
│       └── DESIGN-SPEC.md # Optional
└── shared/               # Shared utilities (hover-overlay, etc.)
```

## Categories

- **data-display**: DataTable, FeedbackCard, StatCard
- **data-visualization**: Chart, PieChart, AmapMap, etc.
- **dev-tools**: ComponentDemoLayout, DevToolbar, DevToolsFAB, PrdAnnotation
- **feedback**: EmptyState, LoadingState, Modal, Spinner, Toast
- **filters**: FilterBar
- **form**: Calendar, DateRangePicker, Form, MultiSelect, Search, Select, Slider
- **general**: Badge, Button, ButtonGroup, DropdownMenu, FAB, Icon, Label, ProgressBar, ToggleSwitch
- **illustrations**: Illustration404
- **layout**: BasicLayout, BentoGrid, SwiperCarousel
- **special**: IndexCard, PlaceholderFeature

## index.ts (Component Root)

```typescript
export { ComponentName } from "./the-component";
export type { ComponentNameProps } from "./the-component";
```

Do **not** export demo pages or `__demo__` content.

## the-component/index.tsx

- Use `React.forwardRef` when the component wraps a DOM element
- Export props as `{ComponentName}Props`
- Use `Component.displayName = "ComponentName"`
- Structure: `// ============ TYPES ============` then `// ============ COMPONENT ============`
- Include JSDoc for props with `@default` when applicable

```typescript
export interface ButtonProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: ButtonVariant;
  /** @default "medium" */
  size?: ButtonSize;
}

export const Button = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(...);
Button.displayName = "Button";
```

## Styles

- Use SCSS modules: `styles.module.scss`
- BEM-like naming: `component-name`, `component-name--variant-*`, `component-name__element`
- Import from `@/` or relative paths: `../../icon` for sibling components

## Category Index

After creating a component, add to the category index:

```typescript
// app/src/components/{category}/index.ts
export { NewComponent } from './new-component';
export type { NewComponentProps } from './new-component';
```
